By that time he preferred to enjoy his performances and those of Mincy in the National Team.
I remember when we beat the United States for the first time during the 1989 Olympic Qualifier in Mexico.
Then came the 1990 World Cup, where we came fourth and it should have been bronze if not for that Canadian referee who made us repeat the final play for the second time, Reyes said.
Is that group from the 1990 World Cup the best National Team you've ever seen?
He is among the best, just like the one that beat the Dream Team in the 2004 Olympics.
But my favorite was the Pan American Games in Cuba in 1991, when we won gold and gave the United States team a fight, which was quite similar to the one that won us bronze in the World Cup.
That team not only repeated Mincy, Gausse, Ramon Rivas, Fico López and "Piculín" (Ortiz), but also had (Javier) "Toñito" Colón and James Carter young, the León brothers (Francisco and Edgar) and Mario "Quixote" Morales, who had not been able to be in the 90 due to a knee injury.
